{
  "doc_id": "15156",
  "text": "Intracellular polysaccharides (IPS) extracted from mycelia and fruiting bodies of mushrooms and exopolysaccharides (EPS) from submerged culture broth have been widely studied and exploited for their multiple pharmacological activities [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Production of EPS in submerged culture has the potential advantages of saving time and space, as well as the possibility of industrial production [CITATION_3] .",
